<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-07-16T17:37:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-07-16T17:37:00-05:00" n="935" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d935">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">396.1 GE/7–1654: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">United States
                                        Delegation</gloss></hi><note n="1" xml:id="d935fn1">Drafted
                                    by the Secretary of State.</note></head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#left"><hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi></seg>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-07-16T18:37:00-04:00">July 16, 1954—6:37
                                        p.m.</date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p><gloss target="#t_Tosec1">Tosec</gloss> 553. For Under Secretary from
                                Secretary. There is rising conern which found utterance at my
                                hearing today with Foreign Relations Committee that vast amounts of
                                war matériel from US will fall into hostile hands. I hope that you
                                will have the opportunity to emphasize to French importance of
                                cease-fire terms which will permit safeguarding or at least
                                destroying this matériel.</p>
                            <p>Hearing as a whole went well and there was no expressed criticism of
                                your return to Geneva.</p>
                            <closer><signed><persName corresp="#p_DJF1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Dulles</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>